Color in life . The dorsum is light buff with long black blotches surrounded by green and yellow edges; the pattern of blotches on the flanks is similar in the specimens examined. Lateral markings are joined from the tympanum to the vent, forming an irregular line; dorsum markings are scarce and lack a regular pattern (
Fig. 1
). Ventrally, males are cream with a reddish-red patch covering part of the abdomen, thighs, and pelvic patch. The throat is yellow. The ventral area has round black blotches small distributed randomly.
